  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Use of vasopressor to maintain Mean Arterial Pressure on Cardio Pulmonary Bypass can lead to
      decreased cerebral flow and oxygenation in individual patients and this can be detected by
      means of cerebral oxymetry.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
